nortelWlanApMib.name: nortelWlanApMib

revisions.description: v005: Added ntWlanDot11TrapTable. Added ntWlanApMuAssocTrap. Added ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrap.

v005: Updates for AP version 1.3.: - Added ntWlanApDot1xAuthenticationFail, ntWlanApMuWEPAuthFail, and ntWlanApMuWPAAuthFail NOTIFICATION-TYPEs. - Added ntWlanApMuAssocTrapEnabled and ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrapEnabled NOTIFICATION-TYPEs. - Added ntWlanApLID, ntWlanApRateSupport, ntWlanApSecurity, ntWlanApQoS, ntWlanApVlan, ntWlanApStats groups. - Added NtWlanApDataRate, NtWlanApWEPKey TEXTUAL-CONVENTIONS. - Added ntWlanSwNNDataFileVer. - Changed enumerations of ntWlanTransferType to ftpDownload(1), tftpDownload(2), ftpUpload(3), and tftpUpload(4). - Added ntWlanFileTransferStatus. - Added ntWlanDot11dWorldModeEnabled and ntWlanDot11ClosedSystem. - Added ntWlanDot118021xBcastKeyRefresh, ntWlanDot118021xSessKeyRefresh, and ntWlanDot118021xReAuthRefresh. - Added ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthServer, ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthPort, ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthKey, ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthRetransmit, and ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthTimeout.

NtWlanApDataRate.name: NtWlanApDataRate
NtWlanApDataRate.description: A data rate, measured in increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s. For example, a value of 2 means a data rate of 1 Mb/s, while a value of 5 means a data rate of 2.5 Mb/s.

NtWlanApWEPKey.name: NtWlanApWEPKey
NtWlanApWEPKey.description: A WEP key. Valid sizes are 5, 13, and 16 octets, corresponding to WEP key lengths of 64, 128, and 152 bits, respectively. A length of 0 is also allowed, so that retrieval of objects containing a valid key value can return an empty string so as to avoid key disclosure.

ntWlanSwHardwareVer.name: ntWlanSwHardwareVer
ntWlanSwHardwareVer.description: Hardware version of the main board.

ntWlanSwBootRomVer.name: ntWlanSwBootRomVer
ntWlanSwBootRomVer.description: Boot ROM code version of the main board.

ntWlanSwOpCodeVer.name: ntWlanSwOpCodeVer
ntWlanSwOpCodeVer.description: Operation code version of the main board.

ntWlanSwNNDataFileVer.name: ntWlanSwNNDataFileVer
ntWlanSwNNDataFileVer.description: Nortel Networks Customization Data File Version.

ntWlanLineTable.name: ntWlanLineTable
ntWlanLineTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each RS-232 line in this system

ntWlanLineEntry.name: ntWlanLineEntry
ntWlanLineEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one RS232 line of the Access Point.

ntWlanLineIndex.name: ntWlanLineIndex
ntWlanLineIndex.description: This is defined as RS-232 index.

ntWlanLineDataBits.name: ntWlanLineDataBits
ntWlanLineDataBits.description: This is defined as number of data bits for the RS232 interface.

ntWlanLineParity.name: ntWlanLineParity
ntWlanLineParity.description: This is defined as parity of the RS232 interface.

ntWlanLineSpeed.name: ntWlanLineSpeed
ntWlanLineSpeed.description: This is defined as the speed of the RS-232 interface.

ntWlanLineStopBits.name: ntWlanLineStopBits
ntWlanLineStopBits.description: This is defined as the number of stop bits for the RS-232 interface.

ntWlanPortTable.name: ntWlanPortTable
ntWlanPortTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each switch port (including expansion slot) in this system. This table also contains information about each trunk (similar to Cisco's EtherChannel).

ntWlanPortEntry.name: ntWlanPortEntry
ntWlanPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one switch port of the switch.

ntWlanPortIndex.name: ntWlanPortIndex
ntWlanPortIndex.description: This is defined as ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

ntWlanPortName.name: ntWlanPortName
ntWlanPortName.description: Indicates the port name. This is same as ifAlias in the IF-MIB (RFC2863 or later).

ntWlanPortSpeedDpxCfg.name: ntWlanPortSpeedDpxCfg
ntWlanPortSpeedDpxCfg.description: Set the port speed and duplex mode as follows: halfDuplex10(2) - 10Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex10(3) - 10Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex100(4) - 100Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex100(5) - 100Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex1000(6) - 1000Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex1000(7) - 1000Mbps and full duplex mode hundredBaseTX port can be set as halfDuplex10(2) fullDuplex10(3) halfDuplex100(4) fullDuplex100(5) hundredBaseFX port can be set as halfDuplex100(4) fullDuplex100(5) thousandBaseSX port can be set as halfDuplex1000(6) fullDuplex1000(7) The actual operating speed and duplex of the port is given by portSpeedDpxStatus.

ntWlanPortFlowCtrlCfg.name: ntWlanPortFlowCtrlCfg
ntWlanPortFlowCtrlCfg.description: (1) Flow control mechanism is enabled. If the port type is hundredBaseTX or thousandBaseSX: When the port is operating in halfDuplex mode, the port uses backPressure flow control mechanism. When the port is operating in fullDuplex mode, the port uses IEEE 802.3x flow control mechanism. If the port type is hundredBaseFX: When the port is operating in halfDuplex mode, the port uses backPressure flow control mechanism. When the port is operating in fullDuplex mode, Flow control mechanism will not function. (2) Flow control mechanism is disabled. (3) Flow control mechanism is backPressure. when the port is in fullDuplex mode.This flow control mechanism will not function. (4) Flow control mechanism is IEEE 802.3x flow control. when the port is in halfDuplex mode.This flow control mechanism will not function. hundredBaseTX and thousandBaseSX port can be set as: enabled(1), disabled(2), backPressure(3), dot3xFlowControl(4). hundredBaseFX port can be set as: enabled(1), disabled(2), backPressure(3). The actual flow control mechanism is used given by portFlowCtrlStatus.

ntWlanPortSpeedDpxStatus.name: ntWlanPortSpeedDpxStatus
ntWlanPortSpeedDpxStatus.description: The operating speed and duplex mode of the switched port. If this index is a trunk, the speed is the speed of its individual members. If this index is a trunk and the result is inconsistent among its member ports, this value is error(1).

ntWlanPortFlowCtrlStatus.name: ntWlanPortFlowCtrlStatus
ntWlanPortFlowCtrlStatus.description: (2) BackPressure flow control machanism is used. (3) IEEE 802.3 flow control machanism is used. (4) Flow control mechanism is disabled. If this index is a trunk and the result is inconsistent among its member ports, this value is error(1).

ntWlanTransferStart.name: ntWlanTransferStart
ntWlanTransferStart.description: Set to go(1) to start a transfer.

ntWlanSrcFile.name: ntWlanSrcFile
ntWlanSrcFile.description: The source file name for TFTP transfer when a transfer is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to the zero length string when no file name has been specified.

ntWlanDestFile.name: ntWlanDestFile
ntWlanDestFile.description: The destination file name for TFTP transfer when a transfer is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to the zero length string when no file name has been specified.

ntWlanFileServer.name: ntWlanFileServer
ntWlanFileServer.description: The IP address of the TFTP server for transfer when a download is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to `0.0.0.0' when no IP address has been specified.

ntWlanUserName.name: ntWlanUserName
ntWlanUserName.description: The username specified for an FTP Transfer.

ntWlanPassword.name: ntWlanPassword
ntWlanPassword.description: The password specified for an FTP Transfer.

ntWlanFileTransferStatus.name: ntWlanFileTransferStatus
ntWlanFileTransferStatus.description: The status of the current FTP Transfer process.

ntWlanRestartOpCodeFile.name: ntWlanRestartOpCodeFile
ntWlanRestartOpCodeFile.description: Name of op-code file for start-up.

ntWlanRestartControl.name: ntWlanRestartControl
ntWlanRestartControl.description: Setting this object to warmBoot(2) causes the device to restart the application software with current configuration parameters saved in non-volatile memory. Setting this object to coldBoot(3) causes the device to reinitialize configuration parameters in non-volatile memory to default values and restart the application software. When the device is running normally, this variable has a value of running(1).

ntWlanNetConfigIPAddress.name: ntWlanNetConfigIPAddress
ntWlanNetConfigIPAddress.description: The IP address of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use DHCP to try to figure out what these values should be. If DHCP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

ntWlanNetConfigSubnetMask.name: ntWlanNetConfigSubnetMask
ntWlanNetConfigSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use DHCP to try to figure out what these values should be. If DHCP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

ntWlanNetDefaultGateway.name: ntWlanNetDefaultGateway
ntWlanNetDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway. If this value is undefined or unknown, it shall have the value 0.0.0.0.

ntWlanDot11PhyOperationTable.name: ntWlanDot11PhyOperationTable
ntWlanDot11PhyOperationTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each radio of the AP.

ntWlanDot11PhyOperationEntry.name: ntWlanDot11PhyOperationEntry
ntWlanDot11PhyOperationEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one radio of the AP.

ntWlanDot11TurboModeEnabled.name: ntWlanDot11TurboModeEnabled
ntWlanDot11TurboModeEnabled.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the nortel's propietory turbo mode option is enabled. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

ntWlanDot11PreambleLength.name: ntWlanDot11PreambleLength
ntWlanDot11PreambleLength.description: This attribute determines whether or not a short or a long preamble is used to delineate 802.11 frames.

ntWlanDot11dWorldModeEnabled.name: ntWlanDot11dWorldModeEnabled
ntWlanDot11dWorldModeEnabled.description: This attribute determines whether 802.11d world mode is enabled for this radio.

ntWlanDot11ClosedSystem.name: ntWlanDot11ClosedSystem
ntWlanDot11ClosedSystem.description: This attribute determines whether the radio operates as a closed system. When configured as a closed system, the SSID is not included when broadcasting periodic beacon frames.

ntWlanDot118021xSupport.name: ntWlanDot118021xSupport
ntWlanDot118021xSupport.description: This attribute, when true(1), indicates that the Enterprise Access Point supports the 802.1x authentication algorithm.

ntWlanDot118021xRequired.name: ntWlanDot118021xRequired
ntWlanDot118021xRequired.description: This attribute, when true(1), indicates that the Enterprise Access Point requires successful 802.1x authentication for any clients accessing the network.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServerTable.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServerTable
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServerTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each authentication server.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServerEntry.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServerEntry
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one radio of the AP.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServer.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServer
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationServer.description: This values indicates the IP address of the authentication server.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationPort.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationPort
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationPort.description: This values indicates the UDP Port used by the primary authentication server.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationKey.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationKey
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationKey.description: This values indicates the shared key used by the authentication server.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationRetransmit.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationRetransmit
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationRetransmit.description: This values indicates the retransmit timer length used by the authentication server.

ntWlanDot11AuthenticationTimeout.name: ntWlanDot11AuthenticationTimeout
ntWlanDot11AuthenticationTimeout.description: This values indicates the Timeout value(sec) used by the authentication server.

ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthServer.name: ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthServer
ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthServer.description: This values indicates the IP address of the secondary authentication server.

ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthPort.name: ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthPort
ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthPort.description: This values indicates the UDP Port used by the primary secondary authentication server.

ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthKey.name: ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthKey
ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthKey.description: This values indicates the shared key used by the secondary authentication server.

ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthRetransmit.name: ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthRetransmit
ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthRetransmit.description: This values indicates the retransmit timer length used by the secondary authentication server.

ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthTimeout.name: ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthTimeout
ntWlanDot11SecondaryAuthTimeout.description: This values indicates the Timeout value(sec) used by the secondary authentication server.

ntWlanDot11FilterTable.name: ntWlanDot11FilterTable
ntWlanDot11FilterTable.description: Table of status information about each configured MAC Address Filtering Entry.

ntWlanDot11FilterEntry.name: ntWlanDot11FilterEntry
ntWlanDot11FilterEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one radio of the AP.

ntWlanDot11FilterAddress.name: ntWlanDot11FilterAddress
ntWlanDot11FilterAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of the filter entry.

ntWlanDot11FilterStatus.name: ntWlanDot11FilterStatus
ntWlanDot11FilterStatus.description: This values indicates the Status of the filter entry. Ifallowed, the client is allowed access to the network. If disallowed, the no frames will be forwarded to the network from the client.

ntWlanDot11TrapTable.name: ntWlanDot11TrapTable
ntWlanDot11TrapTable.description: Table of status information for Association and Disassociation Trap

ntWlanDot11TrapEntry.name: ntWlanDot11TrapEntry
ntWlanDot11TrapEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information for the association and disassociation trap.

ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress.name: ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress
ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of the Mobile Unit associating with this Access Point.

ntWlanDot11DisassociationStationAddress.name: ntWlanDot11DisassociationStationAddress
ntWlanDot11DisassociationStationAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of the Mobile Unit no longer associated with this Access Point.

ntWlanDot11AssociationMU.name: ntWlanDot11AssociationMU
ntWlanDot11AssociationMU.description: This values indicates the number of Mobile Units associated on the Interface

ntWlanApDot1xAuthenticationFail.name: ntWlanApDot1xAuthenticationFail
ntWlanApDot1xAuthenticationFail.description: Indicates that a Mobile Unit failed 802.1x authentication. - ifPhysAddress is the MAC address of the Access Point sending this trap message. - ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress is the MAC address of the Mobile Unit.

ntWlanApMuAssocTrap.name: ntWlanApMuAssocTrap
ntWlanApMuAssocTrap.description: Indicates that there is a Mobile Unit associating with this Access Point. - ifPhysAddress is the MAC address of the Access Point sending this trap message. - ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress is the MAC address of the Mobile Unit. Note: If two or more Mobile Units associate with the Access Point at the same time, ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress belongs to the last Mobile Unit. - ntWlanDot11AssociationMU is the number of Mobile Units currently associating with this Access Point.

ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrap.name: ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrap
ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrap.description: Indicates that there is one Mobile Unit no longer associating with this Access Point anymore. - ifPhysAddress is the MAC address of the Access Point sending this trap message. - ntWlanDot11DisassociationStationAddress is the MAC address of the Mobile Unit. Note: If two or more Mobile Units un-associate with the Access Point at the same time, ntWlanDot11DisassociationStationAddress belongs to the last Mobile Unit. - ntWlanDot11AssociationMU is the number of Mobile Units currently associating with this Access Point.

ntWlanApMuWEPAuthFail.name: ntWlanApMuWEPAuthFail
ntWlanApMuWEPAuthFail.description: Indicates that WEP authentication of a Mobile Unit failed. - ifIndex identifies the radio to which the MU attempted to connect. - ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress is the MAC address of the Mobile Unit that attempted to connect.

ntWlanApMuWPAAuthFail.name: ntWlanApMuWPAAuthFail
ntWlanApMuWPAAuthFail.description: Indicates that WPA authentication of a Mobile Unit failed. - ifIndex identifies the radio to which the MU attempted to connect. - ntWlanDot11AssociationStationAddress is the MAC address of the Mobile Unit that attempted to connect.

ntWlanApMuAssocTrapEnabled.name: ntWlanApMuAssocTrapEnabled
ntWlanApMuAssocTrapEnabled.description: This object controls whether ntWlanApMuAssocTrap notifications will be generated when an MU associates with the AP. If this object is true(1), then the notification will be generated. If it is false, the notification will not be generated.

ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrapEnabled.name: ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrapEnabled
ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrapEnabled.description: This object controls whether ntWlanApMuDisAssocTrap notifications will be generated when an MU disassociates from the AP. If this object is true(1), then the notification will be generated. If it is false, the notification will not be generated.

ntWlanApLIDCheckEtherLinkEnabled.name: ntWlanApLIDCheckEtherLinkEnabled
ntWlanApLIDCheckEtherLinkEnabled.description: Indicates whether checks for ethernet link integrity are enabled.

ntWlanApLIDCheckIPLinkEnabled.name: ntWlanApLIDCheckIPLinkEnabled
ntWlanApLIDCheckIPLinkEnabled.description: Indicates whether checks for IP link integrity are enabled.

ntWlanApLIDCheckIpLinkAddress.name: ntWlanApLIDCheckIpLinkAddress
ntWlanApLIDCheckIpLinkAddress.description: The IP address to ping to check IP link integrity.

ntWlanApRateSupportTable.name: ntWlanApRateSupportTable
ntWlanApRateSupportTable.description: Table to configure which hardware-supported rates are actively supported, and which are basic rates required for an MU to connect to an AP. Entries must exist in this table for every hardware-supported rate for each appropriate ifIndex value.

ntWlanApRateSupportIfIndex.name: ntWlanApRateSupportIfIndex
ntWlanApRateSupportIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the radio.

ntWlanApRateSupportLevel.name: ntWlanApRateSupportLevel
ntWlanApRateSupportLevel.description: This object indicates whether a specific rate is currently supported, and if so, whether it is a basic rate. off - indicates that this rate is not currently supported. supported - indicates that this rate is currently supported, but is not required to be supported by an MU in order to connect to this radio. supportedBasic - indicates that this rate is currently supported as a basic rate, and an MU must also support this rate in order to connect to this radio.

ntWlanApSecurityTable.name: ntWlanApSecurityTable
ntWlanApSecurityTable.description: Table to configure WEP and WPA security parameters. Entries are per-radio.

ntWlanApSecurityIfIndex.name: ntWlanApSecurityIfIndex
ntWlanApSecurityIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the radio.

ntWlanApSecurityEnabled.name: ntWlanApSecurityEnabled
ntWlanApSecurityEnabled.description: Indicates whether security is enabled for a radio.

ntWlanApSecurityWEPKeyLength.name: ntWlanApSecurityWEPKeyLength
ntWlanApSecurityWEPKeyLength.description: Indicates the WEP key length being used.

ntWlanApSecurityWEPActiveKey.name: ntWlanApSecurityWEPActiveKey
ntWlanApSecurityWEPActiveKey.description: Indicates which WEP key is currently in use.

ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey1.name: ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey1
ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey1.description: The first WEP key. Retrieval of this object will always return an empty string.

ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey2.name: ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey2
ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey2.description: The second WEP key. Retrieval of this object will always return an empty string.

ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey3.name: ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey3
ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey3.description: The third WEP key. Retrieval of this object will always return an empty string.

ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey4.name: ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey4
ntWlanApSecurityWEPKey4.description: The fourth WEP key. Retrieval of this object will always return an empty string.

ntWlanApSecurityWPASupport.name: ntWlanApSecurityWPASupport
ntWlanApSecurityWPASupport.description: Indicates whether WPA security is supported.

ntWlanApQoSMode.name: ntWlanApQoSMode
ntWlanApQoSMode.description: This object indicates the QoS mode being used. off - indicates QoS features are disabled. etherSrc - indicates that the ethernet source MAC address of received packets is mapped to an egress queue. etherDst - indicates that the ethernet destination MAC address of received packets is mapped to an egress queue. etherType - indicates that the ethernet type of of received packets is mapped to an egress queue. directPriorityMap - indicates that the priority value of received packets is used to map directly to an egress queue.

ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueTable.name: ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueTable
ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueTable.description: Table to configure mappings from ethernet type to queue number.

ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueIndex.name: ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueIndex
ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueIndex.description: An ethernet type, to be mapped to a queue.

ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueNumber.name: ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueNumber
ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueNumber.description: The queue number to which the ether type is mapped.

ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueRowStatus.name: ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueRowStatus
ntWlanApQoSEtherTypeToQueueRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and destroy entries in this table.

ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueTable.name: ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueTable
ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueTable.description: Table to configure mappings from ethernet MAC address to queue number.

ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueAddress.name: ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueAddress
ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueAddress.description: An ethernet MAC address, to be mapped to a queue.

ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueNumber.name: ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueNumber
ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueNumber.description: The queue number to which the MAC address is mapped.

ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueRowStatus.name: ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueRowStatus
ntWlanApQoSMACToQueueRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and destroy entries in this table.

ntWlanApVlanEnabled.name: ntWlanApVlanEnabled
ntWlanApVlanEnabled.description: This object indicates whether Vlan support is enabled.

ntWlanApVlanTable.name: ntWlanApVlanTable
ntWlanApVlanTable.description: Table to configure the default VID per-radio.

ntWlanApVlanIfIndex.name: ntWlanApVlanIfIndex
ntWlanApVlanIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the radio.

ntWlanApVlanDefaultVid.name: ntWlanApVlanDefaultVid
ntWlanApVlanDefaultVid.description: The default VID of the radio.

ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidTable.name: ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidTable
ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidTable.description: Table containing mappings from Mobile Unit MAC addresses to VLAN ID values.

ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidAddress.name: ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidAddress
ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidAddress.description: The ethernet MAC address of a Mobile Unit.

ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidNumber.name: ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidNumber
ntWlanApVlanMUMACToVidNumber.description: The VID to which this Mobile Unit's MAC is mapped.

ntWlanApMUStatsMUAddress.name: ntWlanApMUStatsMUAddress
ntWlanApMUStatsMUAddress.description: The ethernet MAC address of the Mobile Unit.

ntWlanApMUStatsPacketsIn.name: ntWlanApMUStatsPacketsIn
ntWlanApMUStatsPacketsIn.description: A count of the packets received from this MU.

ntWlanApMUStatsPacketsOut.name: ntWlanApMUStatsPacketsOut
ntWlanApMUStatsPacketsOut.description: A count of the packets sent to this MU.

ntWlanApMUStatsOctetsIn.name: ntWlanApMUStatsOctetsIn
ntWlanApMUStatsOctetsIn.description: A count of the octets received from this MU.

ntWlanApMUStatsOctetsOut.name: ntWlanApMUStatsOctetsOut
ntWlanApMUStatsOctetsOut.description: A count of the octets sent to this MU.
